[[div style="filter: blur(0.03em);"]]
**Item #:** SCP-9085

**Object Class:** --Pending-- ##c90000|What if?##

**Special Containment Procedures:** --As SCP-9085 infection is likely to occur while engaging in normal daily activities, reliable prevention is next to impossible. Once symptoms of SCP-9085 manifest, its mortality rate has been determined to be upwards of 99%.-- ##c90000|I know I'm not dying. I can easily think through how unlikely it is, but I keep thinking //what if what if what if what if what if//, over and over in my head.##

**Description:** SCP-9085 is --an infection of unknown origin with the ability to spread via an extensive list of methods. It is currently unknown whether SCP-9085 is viral, bacterial, or fungal in nature. While exposure is the most common means by which an individual will become infected with SCP-9085, a smaller yet statistically significant proportion of sufferers are-- ##c90000|a defect in my brain. Maybe I was## born with it. ##c90000| I've been like this since I was a child. The idea that I could ever be different feels ridiculous at this point. I wish I was born normal.##

[[/div]]

